{"hash":"b0a1bf1b0bd551c357c2afa394ede44735c37ba9","parent_hashes":["9b5f833346c4dd62e1792ea4112b5dc03bd366ed"],"author":"Alix Trieu","author_email":"atrieu@users.noreply.github.com","date":"2024-04-02T16:40:29+02:00","message_subject":"Joye double-add ladder for short Weierstrass curves in co-Z arithmetic (#1823)","message_body":"* Joye double-add ladder for short Weierstrass curves in co-Z arithmetic\n\n* Use Z.modulo to redefine SS' as suggested by Andres and simplify proofs\n\n* Save some loc\n\n* More comments\n\n* Use sigma types for the Joye ladder\n\n* Use more sigma types and clean up\n\n* Joye ladder: refactor SS, TT\n\n* Simplify HordP\n\n* Use match-goal-with to make proof more readable\n\n* Avoid the +1-1 when defining/using SS/TT as suggested by Andres\n\n* Refactor the ladder\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Alix Trieu <alix@trieu.dev>\nCo-authored-by: Andres Erbsen <andres-github@andres.systems>","files_changed_count":4,"insertions":1689,"deletions":3,"changed_files":["Makefile","src/Curves/Weierstrass/Jacobian/CoZ.v","src/Curves/Weierstrass/{ => Jacobian}/Jacobian.v","src/Curves/Weierstrass/Jacobian/ScalarMult.v"],"coq_files_changed":["src/Curves/Weierstrass/Jacobian/CoZ.v","src/Curves/Weierstrass/{ => Jacobian}/Jacobian.v","src/Curves/Weierstrass/Jacobian/ScalarMult.v"],"touches_proof_files":true,"commit_class":"proof_add","keywords":["weierstrass","by","proof"],"class_confidence":"diff","diff_sorry_removed":false,"diff_net_proof_lines":1682,"tactic_tags":["field","exact","solve","exfalso","apply","progress","destruct","split","repeat","trivial","try","unfold","clear","assert","by","intros","intro","revert","generalize","rewrite","idtac","do","cbv","specialize","simpl","assumption","etransitivity","eauto","auto","eapply","symmetry","nia","lia","exists","pose","case","set","enough","econstructor","cbn","inversion","subst","replace","congruence","right","elim","change","compute","fold","have"],"proof_style":["mixed"]}
{"hash":"8f78fabeaba609dc9cd7728cd55145d3bfbd26f5","parent_hashes":["c2beb201f28878d1eb030b29ec4078ccc1a90a2a"],"author":"Jason Gross","author_email":"jgross@mit.edu","date":"2022-05-19T01:24:08+01:00","message_subject":"Organize and fill out structures and orders (#1234)","message_body":"We're nearly at the point where we can use something like `FMapAVL` to\noptimize `Assembly/Symbolic`.  (Tries would be better, but also harder.)\n\nWhat remains:\n1. `src/Util/FSets/FMapSect` for showing that we don't need a full\n   isomorphism to port FMap structure, only an injection\n2. `src/Util/FSets/FMapOption`\n3. `src/Util/FSets/FMapSum`\n4. `src/Util/FSets/FMapFlip` (maybe?)\n5. `src/Util/FSets/FMapProd`\n6. `src/Util/FSets/FMapListViaAVL` (or similar)\n7. Describing the injection from `op` to something like `N * option\n   AccessSize * option symbol * option N * option N`.\n8. Replacing dag with mapping from `idx` to `node idx * description`,\n   and mapping from `node idx` to `idx`, and an `N` holding the total\n   size of the dag.\n9. Updating corresponding proofs.\n10. (optional) using tries instead of AVL for list-keys","files_changed_count":35,"insertions":2476,"deletions":279,"changed_files":["_CoqProject","src/Assembly/Equivalence.v","src/Assembly/Symbolic.v","src/Stringification/Language.v","src/Util/FSets/{Iso.v => FMapIso.v}","src/Util/{ => FSets}/FMapN.v","src/Util/{ => MSets}/FMapPositive/Equality.v","src/Util/MSets/{Iso.v => MSetIso.v}","src/Util/{ => MSets}/MSetN.v","src/Util/{ => MSets}/MSetPositive/Equality.v","src/Util/{ => MSets}/MSetPositive/Facts.v","src/Util/{ => MSets}/MSetPositive/Show.v","src/Util/MSets/{Sum.v => MSetSum.v}","src/Util/Structures/Equalities.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Bool.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Empty.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/List.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Option.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Prod.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Project.v","src/Util/Structures/Equalities/Sum.v","src/Uti